In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, humans know of 12 gods, evenly split into the two factions: one faction is mostly gods associated with things humans might consider 'good,' though there are a couple of dark gods among them. The other faction is mostly gods associated with things humans would consider 'bad' themed or neutral.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the god of death is part of the good faction.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, to humans, the god of death is enigmatic, but among the gods, he values the old order and views the other faction as upstarts who upset the natural balance of things.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the goddess of shadow is part of the 'good' faction.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the mood and theme of the followers of the goddess of shadow are dark and mysterious, leading other mortals to mistrust them.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the goddess of shadow is ultimately semi-benevolent toward humans.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the goddess of shadow is closely allied with the god of death.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the goddess of shadow is named Nyssara.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the god of death is named Kaelthos.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the goddess of the harvest values mortals more than most gods and is seen as a strong leader among the gods.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the leader of the 'good' gods is the goddess of the harvest, named Mirethra. Mirethra values mortals more than most gods and is seen as a strong leader among the gods. In addition to farmers and laborers, some of her priests are warriors, as they must protect the harvest and the people.

In Dillon's Portal RPGLit book, the protagonist will pledge to Mirethra, the goddess of the harvest, early in the story.
